The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Good Morning
      Hello It's Monday , April 21 , 2008                    
	Whats on    Emergency services, like hospitals, blood banks, medicine shops and hearse services, will be outside the purview of the bandh.    State buses and trams will ply.     Metro Railway will ply as per schedule. But services may be withdrawn depending upon the bandh situation.    Taxis, private buses and autorickshaws will ply, but services may get affected depending upon the bandh situation.    Flights to operate on schedule.    Long-distance and suburban train services of both Eastern and South Eastern Railway will ply as per schedule, provided there is no obstruction on tracks. Adequate security personnel have been deployed to remove obstructions from tracks.    All state and central government departments will be open.    All 19 markets run by the CMC will be open, but shopkeepers may choose to stay away.    Inauguration of Pitaari, a solo exhibition of paintings by Champa Agarwal at The Taj Bengal, 10am.    City Centre will remain open all day.     The chariot of King Khan and his men and women will roll despite the bandh. The stars will be escorted to the airport to catch the 2.30pm Jet Airways flight to Mumbai.     
	Whats off    Calcutta Universitys B.A., B.Sc., and B.Com. Part III Honours sixth paper has been postponed to Tuesday. The timings and the venues will remain unchanged.    All major art galleries will be closed.    
	Post-bandh     South City Mall will open once the bandh is lifted.    Fame (South City) will open at 6pm, after the bandh is called off.     Fame (Hiland Park) will open at 2pm.    INOX Forum will open for the 5.10pm.    INOX City Centre will open for the 5.05pm.    89 Cinemas will open at 4.20pm.    Adlabs in Sector V will open at 6pm.                                                                                                                                                              
